    "content": "<p>A cylindrical bar has a length 𝐿 = 5 𝑚 and cross section area 𝑆 = 10 𝑚<sup>2</sup> . The bar is made of a linear elastic material with a density ρ = 2700 kg/m<sup>3</sup> and Young’s modulus E = 70 GPa. The bar is suspended as shown in the figure and is in a state of uniaxial tension due to its self-weight.</p>\n\n<p>The elastic strain energy stored in the bar equals _________ J. (Rounded off to two decimal places)</p>\n\n<p>Take the acceleration due to gravity as 𝑔 = 9.8 m/s<sup>2</sup>.</p>\n\n<p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1lz3rxr71/5a424212-12bf-49b1-9270-4a04fcbd1a72/cb5d49d0-4be4-11ef-a793-e1425336250e/file-jaoe38c1lz3rxr72.webp?format=webp\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1lz3rxr71/5a424212-12bf-49b1-9270-4a04fcbd1a72/cb5d49d0-4be4-11ef-a793-e1425336250e/file-jaoe38c1lz3rxr72.webp\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"GATE ME 2023 Strength of Materials - Strain Energy Method Question 2 English\"></p>\n",
    "options": [],
    "correct_options": [],
    "explanation": "<img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1lz3s14y0/2fced7a5-671b-458b-bf14-ddbe8a802695/2969ac80-4be5-11ef-a793-e1425336250e/file-jaoe38c1lz3s14y1.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1lz3s14y0/2fced7a5-671b-458b-bf14-ddbe8a802695/2969ac80-4be5-11ef-a793-e1425336250e/file-jaoe38c1lz3s14y1.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"GATE ME 2023 Strength of Materials - Strain Energy Method Question 2 English Explanation\">\n<p>Strain energy $=\\frac{1}{2}(\\sigma \\varepsilon) \\times$ Volume</p>\n\n<p>$$ \\begin{aligned} &amp; \\text { Strain energy }=\\frac{1}{2}\\left(\\frac{\\sigma^2}{E}\\right) \\times \\text { Volume } \\\\\\\\ &amp; \\sigma=\\frac{(\\rho A x) g}{A}=\\rho x g \\\\\\\\ &amp; d u=\\frac{\\rho^2 x^2 g^2}{2 E} \\times A d x \\\\\\\\ &amp; U=\\frac{\\rho^2 g^2 A}{2 E} \\int\\limits_0^h x^2 d x=2.088 \\mathrm{~J} \\end{aligned} $$</p>\n\n<p>Hence, the correct answer is 2.088 J .</p>",
